longBusinessSummary: Toyo Seikan Group Holdings, Ltd. manufactures and sells packaging containers in Japan and internationally. The company operates through four segments: Packaging Business, Steel Plate Related Business, Functional Materials Related Business, and Real Estate Related Business. It offers packaging containers, such as metal cans, plastic containers, caps, bottles, paper containers, and aerosol products, as well as packaging-related machinery and equipment. The company also provides steel-plate-related products, such as materials for cans, electrical and electronic components, automobile and industry machinery parts, and household electronic appliances, as well as construction materials. In addition, it offers functional materials comprising aluminum substrates for magnetic disks, functional films for optics, glosts, micro-element fertilizers, pigments, and gel coats. Further, the company provides machinery and equipment related with packaging containers consisting of container manufacturing equipment, and filling and seaming equipment; and hard alloys, machinery and appliances, and raw material products for agriculture, as well as stamping dies for automotive parts. Additionally, it is involved in the motor truck transportation and warehousing business; non-life insurance agency real estate management businesses; leasing of properties comprising office buildings and commercial facilities; and sale of petroleum products. The company was formerly known as Toyo Seikan Kaisha, Ltd. and changed its name to Toyo Seikan Group Holdings, Ltd. in April 2013. Toyo Seikan Group Holdings, Ltd. was founded in 1917 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
